apiDescription: An enumeration of possible errors associated with a TryLockResult which can occur while trying to acquire a lock, from the try_lock method on a Mutex or the try_read and try_write methods on an RwLock.

enum variants:
The lock could not be acquired because another thread failed while holding
the lock.

The lock could not be acquired at this time because the operation would
otherwise block.

trait implementations.name: impl<T> std::marker::Send for std::sync::TryLockError<T> where T: std::marker::Send
impl<T> std::marker::Sync for std::sync::TryLockError<T> where T: std::marker::Sync
